And we ended our last segment
with some really sad things

00:11:07.780 --> 00:11:11.170 align:middle line:84%
that you were talking about,
that this global warming

00:11:11.170 --> 00:11:13.215 align:middle line:90%
is actually causing disease.

00:11:13.215 --> 00:11:16.900 align:middle line:84%
>> It's causing tropical
diseases to move north

00:11:16.900 --> 00:11:17.860 align:middle line:90%
into temperate regions.

00:11:17.860 --> 00:11:20.245 align:middle line:84%
Like New York City had an
outbreak of Nile encephalitis.

00:11:20.245 --> 00:11:23.860 align:middle line:84%
It was because a West
Nile mosquito suddenly

00:11:23.860 --> 00:11:27.220 align:middle line:90%
moved in to New York City.

00:11:27.220 --> 00:11:29.500 align:middle line:84%
Normally, a cold winter
would kill this mosquito

00:11:29.500 --> 00:11:30.910 align:middle line:84%
because it's used
to the tropics.

00:11:30.910 --> 00:11:33.010 align:middle line:84%
However, the winter
was too mild,

00:11:33.010 --> 00:11:34.550 align:middle line:90%
the mosquitoes are still around.

00:11:34.550 --> 00:11:38.290 align:middle line:84%
They've now appeared in
my home state of Virginia,

00:11:38.290 --> 00:11:40.052 align:middle line:90%
near Washington DC.

00:11:40.052 --> 00:11:43.890 align:middle line:84%
>> So this is no longer
something we can just look

00:11:43.890 --> 00:11:45.520 align:middle line:90%
at for the future?

00:11:45.520 --> 00:11:47.640 align:middle line:90%
>> No.

00:11:47.640 --> 00:11:51.040 align:middle line:84%
Here in Chicago, you lost
800 people in-- what is it--

00:11:51.040 --> 00:11:54.510 align:middle line:84%
three days to a
killer heat wave.

00:11:54.510 --> 00:11:57.400 align:middle line:84%
That is the face of global
warming we're going to see.

00:11:57.400 --> 00:12:03.480 align:middle line:84%
>> In '98, 5% of the world's
population were displaced from

00:12:03.480 --> 00:12:06.720 align:middle line:84%
their homes at one
period of time or another

00:12:06.720 --> 00:12:09.150 align:middle line:90%
because of climatic problems.

00:12:09.150 --> 00:12:12.300 align:middle line:90%
So it's really affecting us now.

00:12:12.300 --> 00:12:15.840 align:middle line:90%
We're just seeing the beginning.

00:12:15.840 --> 00:12:18.330 align:middle line:84%
As the carbon increases,
we'll continue

00:12:18.330 --> 00:12:21.540 align:middle line:84%
to see more unless we
turn this problem around.

00:12:21.540 --> 00:12:24.540 align:middle line:84%
>> You know, I think that
this is a very important book

00:12:24.540 --> 00:12:26.760 align:middle line:84%
because I think most
people, including myself,

00:12:26.760 --> 00:12:28.830 align:middle line:84%
think that this is
something that is way,

00:12:28.830 --> 00:12:32.820 align:middle line:84%
way out in the future and
we've got plenty of time to do

00:12:32.820 --> 00:12:34.043 align:middle line:90%
something about it.

00:12:34.043 --> 00:12:35.460 align:middle line:84%
But you're saying
the time is now.

00:12:35.460 --> 00:12:36.260 align:middle line:90%
>> Time is now.

00:12:36.260 --> 00:12:37.653 align:middle line:90%
>> What can we do?

00:12:37.653 --> 00:12:39.320 align:middle line:84%
What's the first thing
to be done, John?

00:12:39.320 --> 00:12:44.880 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, we proposed a 10-point
plan to start action now,

00:12:44.880 --> 00:12:48.000 align:middle line:90%
to change this course we are on.

00:12:48.000 --> 00:12:50.940 align:middle line:10%
The first thing we can do
is revive the fusion energy

00:12:50.940 --> 00:12:52.500 align:middle line:10%
program we had in this country.

00:12:52.500 --> 00:12:55.440 align:middle line:10%
We passed a fusion energy,
Magnetic Fusion Energy

00:12:55.440 --> 00:12:58.110 align:middle line:10%
Engineering Act in
1980, President Carter.

00:12:58.110 --> 00:13:01.200 align:middle line:84%
It was going to give us fusion
energy in 10 years, power

00:13:01.200 --> 00:13:02.370 align:middle line:90%
into the grid.

00:13:02.370 --> 00:13:04.215 align:middle line:84%
Fusion is a much
safer, cleaner form--

00:13:04.215 --> 00:13:05.015 align:middle line:90%
>> What is it?

00:13:05.015 --> 00:13:09.030 align:middle line:84%
>> Fusion is the nuclear process
that gives light to the stars

00:13:09.030 --> 00:13:10.110 align:middle line:90%
and the sun.

00:13:10.110 --> 00:13:12.930 align:middle line:84%
It is the process that
allows the universe

00:13:12.930 --> 00:13:15.460 align:middle line:84%
to have warmth and
light and life.

00:13:15.460 --> 00:13:18.480 align:middle line:84%
So it's a very
natural energy cycle.

00:13:18.480 --> 00:13:21.900 align:middle line:84%
>> And it's very different than
the kind of nuclear energy that

00:13:21.900 --> 00:13:26.820 align:middle line:84%
we're using now, which is unsafe
and produces long-term waste

00:13:26.820 --> 00:13:29.080 align:middle line:84%
that are extremely
hard to deal with.

00:13:29.080 --> 00:13:32.580 align:middle line:84%
So this is a much safer,
much more natural form

00:13:32.580 --> 00:13:38.370 align:middle line:84%
of nuclear energy, and one of
the keystones of our proposal.

00:13:38.370 --> 00:13:44.580 align:middle line:84%
We also are proposing that we
actually exchange debt or pay

00:13:44.580 --> 00:13:48.300 align:middle line:84%
rainforest nations
to produce trees.

00:13:48.300 --> 00:13:50.130 align:middle line:84%
Right now, they don't
have any incentive

00:13:50.130 --> 00:13:52.200 align:middle line:90%
to keep the rainforest intact.

00:13:52.200 --> 00:13:55.710 align:middle line:84%
These are poor people,
they need to farm,

00:13:55.710 --> 00:13:59.700 align:middle line:84%
they tear down the rainforest
in order to have farmland.

00:13:59.700 --> 00:14:04.680 align:middle line:84%
But if we actually generated
another motivation for them

00:14:04.680 --> 00:14:08.250 align:middle line:84%
to keep the rainforest
standing to plant trees

00:14:08.250 --> 00:14:11.900 align:middle line:84%
and maintain them, we
would be better off.

00:14:11.900 --> 00:14:15.560 align:middle line:84%
We have a number of other
solutions, many of which

00:14:15.560 --> 00:14:19.790 align:middle line:84%
your viewers can begin to
take action on right away.

00:14:19.790 --> 00:14:22.700 align:middle line:84%
One level is we need
to begin to demand

00:14:22.700 --> 00:14:25.100 align:middle line:90%
that our leadership lead us.

00:14:25.100 --> 00:14:27.740 align:middle line:10%
We need to tell our
leaders to lead us

00:14:27.740 --> 00:14:29.840 align:middle line:10%
in the instance
of global warming.

00:14:29.840 --> 00:14:33.290 align:middle line:10%
This is a planetary
problem we need leadership.

00:14:33.290 --> 00:14:34.690 align:middle line:90%
>> What's blocking it?

00:14:34.690 --> 00:14:39.140 align:middle line:84%
>> We have an opportunity right
now because this country has

00:14:39.140 --> 00:14:43.970 align:middle line:84%
had no energy policy since 1980
because of the oil glut that

00:14:43.970 --> 00:14:46.640 align:middle line:84%
occurred in the Middle East when
Iran and Iraq began their war

00:14:46.640 --> 00:14:49.160 align:middle line:90%
with each other.

00:14:49.160 --> 00:14:50.870 align:middle line:84%
So we didn't need to
think about energy.

00:14:50.870 --> 00:14:53.210 align:middle line:84%
It was just like turning
on water on the tap.

00:14:53.210 --> 00:14:56.560 align:middle line:84%
Now, we have an opportunity
with OPEC price increases

00:14:56.560 --> 00:15:00.210 align:middle line:84%
to actually address the problem
of energy and global warming.

00:15:00.210 --> 00:15:02.360 align:middle line:84%
We need appropriate
energy sources.

00:15:02.360 --> 00:15:06.992 align:middle line:84%
And if we can use solar and
wind to the maximum that we can

00:15:06.992 --> 00:15:09.200 align:middle line:84%
because those are available
right now, if we develop,

00:15:09.200 --> 00:15:14.150 align:middle line:84%
we reinvigorate, we revive
the 10-year program to harness

00:15:14.150 --> 00:15:19.820 align:middle line:84%
fusion power so we have cleaner,
safer energy in massive amounts

00:15:19.820 --> 00:15:22.820 align:middle line:84%
for the future and we
electrify the cars,

00:15:22.820 --> 00:15:26.765 align:middle line:84%
and we replant the rainforests,
then this great tragedy--

00:15:26.765 --> 00:15:27.965 align:middle line:90%
>> We can save the Earth.

00:15:27.965 --> 00:15:28.820 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes, we can.

00:15:28.820 --> 00:15:31.760 align:middle line:84%
>> Once you begin
to face a problem,

00:15:31.760 --> 00:15:34.940 align:middle line:84%
then all sorts of creative
resources become available

00:15:34.940 --> 00:15:36.080 align:middle line:90%
to solve it.

00:15:36.080 --> 00:15:38.810 align:middle line:84%
We've solved other
horrific problems here

00:15:38.810 --> 00:15:41.130 align:middle line:90%
on this planet, the dust bowl.

00:15:41.130 --> 00:15:43.040 align:middle line:90%
We've gotten a man on the moon.

00:15:43.040 --> 00:15:44.680 align:middle line:90%
We can solve this one too.

00:15:44.680 --> 00:15:47.030 align:middle line:84%
>> But what does the
ordinary person do here?

00:15:47.030 --> 00:15:50.570 align:middle line:84%
They're sitting there thinking,
"oh my god, this is terrible.

00:15:50.570 --> 00:15:51.440 align:middle line:90%
What can I do?"

00:15:51.440 --> 00:15:53.360 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, they make
choices all the time.

00:15:53.360 --> 00:15:55.010 align:middle line:84%
When they buy a
vehicle, they can

00:15:55.010 --> 00:15:57.370 align:middle line:90%
buy more fuel-efficient one.

00:15:57.370 --> 00:16:01.460 align:middle line:84%
When they buy an appliance, they
can look for fuel-efficiency

00:16:01.460 --> 00:16:03.110 align:middle line:90%
as part of the package.

00:16:03.110 --> 00:16:05.390 align:middle line:84%
They can also
insulate their homes,

00:16:05.390 --> 00:16:07.760 align:middle line:84%
begin to implement
solar energy if that's

00:16:07.760 --> 00:16:10.940 align:middle line:90%
a possibility for them.

00:16:10.940 --> 00:16:13.910 align:middle line:84%
Fuel cell driven
vehicles are coming

00:16:13.910 --> 00:16:16.820 align:middle line:84%
online in the next two
or three four years.

00:16:16.820 --> 00:16:20.420 align:middle line:84%
We can be receptive
to that as consumers

00:16:20.420 --> 00:16:22.940 align:middle line:84%
and buy the kinds
of things that are

00:16:22.940 --> 00:16:25.820 align:middle line:90%
going to produce less carbon.

00:16:25.820 --> 00:16:31.160 align:middle line:84%
But we can also
support an initiative

00:16:31.160 --> 00:16:35.600 align:middle line:84%
to end global warming
by asking our Congress

00:16:35.600 --> 00:16:39.770 align:middle line:84%
people to support the
passing of the Kyoto Accord.

00:16:39.770 --> 00:16:40.925 align:middle line:90%
>> What is that?

00:16:40.925 --> 00:16:48.170 align:middle line:84%
>> That is an international
effort to use a rational

00:16:48.170 --> 00:16:52.430 align:middle line:84%
and just approach to solving
the problem of global warming,

00:16:52.430 --> 00:16:57.500 align:middle line:84%
and it asks for countries
to reduce to a certain limit

00:16:57.500 --> 00:16:59.360 align:middle line:84%
the amount of carbon
that they're putting

00:16:59.360 --> 00:17:01.160 align:middle line:90%
into the atmosphere.

00:17:01.160 --> 00:17:06.140 align:middle line:84%
And it's not perfect
and nothing is perfect

00:17:06.140 --> 00:17:11.270 align:middle line:84%
but it is an equitable
and an initial step

00:17:11.270 --> 00:17:13.670 align:middle line:90%
that people can take right now.

00:17:13.670 --> 00:17:20.930 align:middle line:84%
As well as voting for the
kinds of representation

00:17:20.930 --> 00:17:23.630 align:middle line:84%
that we'll have that
treats global warming

00:17:23.630 --> 00:17:24.520 align:middle line:90%
as a serious problem.

00:17:24.520 --> 00:17:28.240 align:middle line:90%
>> What has stopped the process?

00:17:28.240 --> 00:17:29.240 align:middle line:90%
The glut of oil?

00:17:29.240 --> 00:17:32.640 align:middle line:84%
>> Yes, the glut of oil, but
also the fact that people think

00:17:32.640 --> 00:17:33.440 align:middle line:90%
they are helpless.

00:17:33.440 --> 00:17:35.553 align:middle line:84%
They don't think
they have options.

00:17:35.553 --> 00:17:37.220 align:middle line:84%
Part of what we tried
to do in this book

00:17:37.220 --> 00:17:40.850 align:middle line:84%
is help people face the problem
squarely without flinching,

00:17:40.850 --> 00:17:43.640 align:middle line:84%
but also face their
options squarely.

00:17:43.640 --> 00:17:47.390 align:middle line:84%
They have options they
don't know that they have.

00:17:47.390 --> 00:17:50.840 align:middle line:84%
Many people feel like the
choice is between an environment

00:17:50.840 --> 00:17:51.920 align:middle line:90%
or an economy.

00:17:51.920 --> 00:17:54.410 align:middle line:84%
And basically, that
isn't a choice.

00:17:54.410 --> 00:17:56.540 align:middle line:84%
What we have to do is
environmental policy

00:17:56.540 --> 00:17:58.850 align:middle line:84%
that helps the economy
continue to grow and provide

00:17:58.850 --> 00:18:00.590 align:middle line:84%
employment, not
only for ourselves

00:18:00.590 --> 00:18:02.010 align:middle line:90%
but the rest of the world.

00:18:02.010 --> 00:18:05.840 align:middle line:84%
We also need economic
policies, energy policies

00:18:05.840 --> 00:18:08.585 align:middle line:84%
that bring us more in
tune with the environment,

00:18:08.585 --> 00:18:09.460 align:middle line:90%
not fight against it.

00:18:09.460 --> 00:18:12.320 align:middle line:84%
>> The only frightening thing
here is that you talked about

00:18:12.320 --> 00:18:15.980 align:middle line:84%
the lack of oxygen now on the
air and the children who are--

00:18:15.980 --> 00:18:18.560 align:middle line:84%
so many more children have
asthma now than ever before.

00:18:18.560 --> 00:18:21.860 align:middle line:84%
>> There really is a
worldwide epidemic of asthma.

00:18:21.860 --> 00:18:24.890 align:middle line:84%
It's a bit of a mystery
why this is happening.

00:18:24.890 --> 00:18:27.980 align:middle line:84%
They do know that air
quality is one of the factors

00:18:27.980 --> 00:18:31.730 align:middle line:84%
and they've identified a number
of gases that are a problem.

00:18:31.730 --> 00:18:35.520 align:middle line:84%
Of course, oxygen is
going down on our planet.

00:18:35.520 --> 00:18:39.380 align:middle line:84%
We don't think that that's
directly a factor in asthma

00:18:39.380 --> 00:18:40.950 align:middle line:90%
because it's such a small part.

00:18:40.950 --> 00:18:41.850 align:middle line:90%
>> Real tiny, tiny.

00:18:41.850 --> 00:18:42.650 align:middle line:90%
>> Tiny part.

00:18:42.650 --> 00:18:45.350 align:middle line:84%
On the other hand,
this is one, it's

00:18:45.350 --> 00:18:48.680 align:middle line:84%
a red light going off
on your dashboard.

00:18:48.680 --> 00:18:51.560 align:middle line:84%
It's really the planet's way
of telling us that things

00:18:51.560 --> 00:18:53.780 align:middle line:90%
are trending in a bad way.

00:18:53.780 --> 00:18:57.920 align:middle line:84%
They are going in
a direction that we

00:18:57.920 --> 00:19:01.160 align:middle line:84%
need to take the car into
the shop and get it fixed

00:19:01.160 --> 00:19:03.930 align:middle line:84%
or will cause more serious
and permanent damage.

00:19:03.930 --> 00:19:07.970 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, for years, we've been
hearing about electric cars

00:19:07.970 --> 00:19:09.525 align:middle line:84%
and they show them
at auto shows.

00:19:09.525 --> 00:19:10.325 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:19:10.325 --> 00:19:11.300 align:middle line:90%
>> But nothing happens.

00:19:11.300 --> 00:19:12.100 align:middle line:90%
Why?

00:19:12.100 --> 00:19:14.990 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, they're expensive
and part of it is,

00:19:14.990 --> 00:19:17.420 align:middle line:84%
is until they can have
production lines that are

00:19:17.420 --> 00:19:19.923 align:middle line:84%
producing electric
cars all the time,

00:19:19.923 --> 00:19:21.590 align:middle line:84%
and people are buying
them all the time,

00:19:21.590 --> 00:19:23.840 align:middle line:90%
the cost will not come down.

00:19:23.840 --> 00:19:26.740 align:middle line:84%
Also, we have to develop
some infrastructures.

00:19:26.740 --> 00:19:28.490 align:middle line:84%
Fortunately, all of
our houses are already

00:19:28.490 --> 00:19:29.930 align:middle line:90%
wired for electricity.

00:19:29.930 --> 00:19:31.820 align:middle line:84%
The gas stations
could also convert

00:19:31.820 --> 00:19:35.690 align:middle line:84%
to supplying electricity
instead of gasoline.

00:19:35.690 --> 00:19:38.435 align:middle line:84%
But there's some
reorganization that we have to,

00:19:38.435 --> 00:19:40.670 align:middle line:84%
to make an electric
car friendly society.

00:19:40.670 --> 00:19:44.300 align:middle line:84%
>> It also is going
to be up to consumers.

00:19:44.300 --> 00:19:47.390 align:middle line:10%
When we discovered that
the SFCs were creating

00:19:47.390 --> 00:19:51.920 align:middle line:10%
a hole in the ozone layer,
there was a consumer movement

00:19:51.920 --> 00:19:57.290 align:middle line:10%
along with scientists to stop
buying aerosol spray cans.

00:19:57.290 --> 00:20:01.430 align:middle line:84%
So when consumers
begin to actually look

00:20:01.430 --> 00:20:06.350 align:middle line:84%
at what their vehicles
are costing them

00:20:06.350 --> 00:20:08.720 align:middle line:84%
in terms of the future
for their children

00:20:08.720 --> 00:20:11.810 align:middle line:84%
and begin to have alternatives
that are realistically

00:20:11.810 --> 00:20:15.602 align:middle line:84%
available to them, I think
people will do the right thing.

00:20:15.602 --> 00:20:18.230 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, I think especially
if they realize that these

00:20:18.230 --> 00:20:22.460 align:middle line:84%
problems are directly affecting
our generation, our children,

00:20:22.460 --> 00:20:25.620 align:middle line:84%
our grandchildren, and not some
future generation that let them

00:20:25.620 --> 00:20:26.420 align:middle line:90%
worry about it.

00:20:26.420 --> 00:20:29.130 align:middle line:84%
>> This isn't something that's
going to happen 100 years from

00:20:29.130 --> 00:20:29.930 align:middle line:90%
now.

00:20:29.930 --> 00:20:32.680 align:middle line:84%
This is something that's
happening right now.

00:20:32.680 --> 00:20:36.710 align:middle line:84%
We are going to see more
flooding, more hurricanes, more

00:20:36.710 --> 00:20:42.200 align:middle line:84%
tornadoes, more tropical
diseases, more droughts

00:20:42.200 --> 00:20:44.060 align:middle line:90%
as a result of global warming.

00:20:44.060 --> 00:20:47.480 align:middle line:84%
And this is something that will
affect our insurance rates,

00:20:47.480 --> 00:20:50.840 align:middle line:84%
it will affect our
economies, it will--

00:20:50.840 --> 00:20:54.020 align:middle line:84%
it is potentially
very catastrophic

00:20:54.020 --> 00:20:57.530 align:middle line:84%
for individuals and
certainly for a whole planet.

00:20:57.530 --> 00:21:01.190 align:middle line:84%
So everyone needs to know
that the choices that they

00:21:01.190 --> 00:21:04.595 align:middle line:84%
make, the people that they
vote for make a difference.

00:21:04.595 --> 00:21:06.470 align:middle line:84%
>> And they should be
asking these questions.

00:21:06.470 --> 00:21:07.270 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:21:07.270 --> 00:21:08.442 align:middle line:90%
>> Absolutely.

00:21:08.442 --> 00:21:12.310 align:middle line:84%
>> What are you going to
do about the environment?

00:21:12.310 --> 00:21:15.490 align:middle line:84%
>> By reducing our
dependence on foreign oil,

00:21:15.490 --> 00:21:18.910 align:middle line:84%
we'll increase our security
of our economy and also

00:21:18.910 --> 00:21:20.300 align:middle line:90%
our national security.

00:21:20.300 --> 00:21:22.450 align:middle line:84%
We don't want to have
to go to war again

00:21:22.450 --> 00:21:25.993 align:middle line:84%
over oil supplies that are
coming from across the ocean.

00:21:25.993 --> 00:21:27.910 align:middle line:84%
It would be much better
to have energy sources

00:21:27.910 --> 00:21:31.240 align:middle line:84%
here in this country supplying
most of our energy needs.

00:21:31.240 --> 00:21:34.300 align:middle line:84%
At the same time,
if we get a few--

00:21:34.300 --> 00:21:36.280 align:middle line:84%
more hurricane
Andrews in Florida

00:21:36.280 --> 00:21:39.880 align:middle line:84%
and the Gulf states
and the South Atlantic

00:21:39.880 --> 00:21:42.970 align:middle line:84%
